history.content:
Last semester, I took CS 162 + CS 161 + Breadth and was also heavily recruiting. It was definitely manageable but generally the first portion of CS 161 is a bit more of a heavy workload compared to the rest of the semester (which is the hot-recruiting time) so that's something to keep in mind. Just make sure to stay on top of material in both classes (work on projects, go to discussions, etc). 

I would recommend CS 162 + CS 168 + breadth or CS 162 + CS 161 + Breadth. Especially with CS 161 and CS 162 you'll find a good overlap in content (especially in the beginning). CS 168 is a light workload class which is a good class to take with CS 162 as they're in similar areas. Both of these schedules I mentioned above are some schedules I know where you'll learn a lot of material (so long as you're motivated and keep up with the material).

As far as CS 188 and DS 100 goes, in my opinion, there isn't much overlap. I took both courses and found that both courses had different areas of focus so I wouldn't worry too much about redundancy. If you are taking CS 189, you might find DS 100 teaches more high-level, and library-implementations of ML algorithms (at least that's how I felt about it). 

Hope this answers your questions.

children.subject: To the student's response above, would taking 162, 161, and 168 plus the 1 unit Ethics requirement be overkill? (I'll also be recruiting for full-time jobs)
<md>I believe 189 and data 100 is more redundant than 188 + data 100</md>

history.content:
Background
Hi. My question is sort of Multi pronged. So my tentative schedule idea for fall 2020 is either:
A. 162, DS 100, breadth
B. 162, 188, breadth
C. 162, 188, DS 100
D. 162, another upperdiv EE/CS, breadth
I already have a group for 162, and I’ll also be recruiting (pretty heavily I’d say) during next semester. 

My questions
1. Which is the most manageable while still learning something schedule?
2. Are 188/DS 100 redundant? I’ve heard some people say stuff like that before, and if they are which do you tend towards?
3. I’m considering taking 189 spring 2021, do either data 100/188 become redundant after taking 189.
4. If I go with option D, what other upper divs would be manageable? (do any of 161,186,126/127 sound ok)
